track.name: Out of Nowhere
comments: The brilliant saxophonist who became at the origins of modern jazz.
WHEN BIRD WAS RIGHT THERE WAS NO ONE LIKE HIM. A LEGEND OF JAZZ R I P  BIRD
sensitive and soulful as any sax could be
Beauty of sound and sensuality as well:Charlie 'Yardbird" Parker was the man!
do I have to say anything :-)
the music is love of Charlie....
Is a night walk.......... moon, and sweet rain!
Every time I listen to Bird I dicover new things in his blowing. I hear a great line from Getz, or Cannonball, and then I listen to Bird and realize he did it first.

Nowhere does not exist!!! It must come from somewhere!!!! Music comes from Bird. Bird sings. We hear. I, for one, am happy he played with great generousity of spirit and love. I feel it. Thankyou Bird.
